00:39:53.699 --> 00:39:58.699
Like, you shouldn't probably go into a conversation and say, Shiny should replace this.

00:39:58.699 --> 00:40:00.699
There's a lot of things you'll find.

00:40:00.699 --> 00:40:10.699
Even if the leadership supports that, you'll find there's a lot of things that, you know, IT support and human resources that can do all the work and all that kind of stuff comes into play.

00:40:10.699 --> 00:40:21.699
So the conversation I found is more helpful is when you can demonstrate what something like Shiny can do that those tools can't or, you know, the use case for those.

00:40:21.699 --> 00:40:25.699
Or, you know, like serving up model scores through Plumber API and RStudio Connect.

00:40:25.699 --> 00:40:32.699
